modules.description: This module provides functions to read and parse files containing metadata in TOML format. It supports extracting structured data from files using customizable strategies and returns results as typed values. Concrete use cases include loading configuration files or document metadata during static site generation.

This module provides functions to read and parse files containing metadata described by a specific type `t`, using TOML format. It supports extracting metadata from either source or target files, with optional custom extraction strategies. Concrete use cases include loading configuration data from TOML files during static site generation or processing metadata embedded in source documents.

This module provides functions to parse TOML-formatted metadata from strings and convert it into a standardized data type for further processing. It includes specialized submodules for handling file-based metadata extraction and pipeline integration, supporting customizable parsing strategies. Concrete use cases include loading and normalizing configuration data from TOML files during static site generation workflows.
